<section xml:id="sec_fifth-examplesA" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Examples A</title>
  
<example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      A man pushes a cart on a railway platform which has a rough surface. 
      He applies a force of 100 N over a distance of 10 m. Thereafter, he 
      gets tired and his force reduces gradually to 50 N. The total distance 
      through which the cart has been moved is 20 m. Plot the force applied by 
      the man and the frictional force of 50N versus displacement. Calculate the 
      work done by the man and the frictional force.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      Work done by a man = Area under the F-x curve. 
      <image source="ec5.png" width="30%"> </image> 
      Therefore <m>W_{m}</m> = Area of a rectangle I +Area of a trapezium II. 
      <me>
        W_{m} = \left(100\times10\right)+\left(\frac{1}{2} (100+50)\times10\right) =1750 J
      </me>
      Work done by a frictional force, <m>W_{f}</m>= Area of a rectangle III. 
      <me>
        W_{f} =  \left(-50\times20\right) = -1000 J
      </me>
       </p>
  </solution>
</example>

<example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Given the vectors 
      <me>
        \vec{A}  =  3 \hat{i} + 4 \hat{j}
      </me>
       and 
       <me>
        \vec{B} =  \hat{i} - 2 \hat{j} + 2 \hat{k}
       </me>
       Find 
       <ol marker="a.">
        <li>
          the magnitude of each vector and
        </li>
        <li>
          the angle between them.
        </li>
       </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <ol marker="a.">
        <li>
          <me>
            A^{2}  = \vec{A} \cdot\vec{A}  =  3^{2} + 4^{2} = 25;
          </me>
          <me>
            \therefore A  =  \sqrt{25}=5
          </me>
          <me>
            B^{2}  =  \vec{B} \cdot\vec{B}  =  (1)^{2} + (-2)^{2} + 2^{2}  = 9;
          </me>
          <me>
            \therefore B  =  \sqrt{9}=3.
          </me>
          </li>
        <li>
         <me>
          \vec{A} \cdot\vec{B}   =  A B \cos\theta 
         </me>
         or,
         <me>
          A_{x}B_{x}+A_{y}B_{y}+A_{z}B_{z} = \left[\sqrt{A^{2}_{x}+A^{2}_{y}+A^{2}_{z}} \sqrt{B^{2}_{x}+B^{2}_{y}+B^{2}_{z}}\right]\cos\theta
         </me>
         or, 
         <me>
           (3)(1) + (4)(-2) + (0)(2)= \sqrt{9+16+0}\sqrt{1+4+4}\cos\theta
         </me>
         <me>
          \text{or,}\quad -5 = 15\cos\theta \quad \Rightarrow \quad \cos\theta = -\frac{1}{3} 
         </me>
         <me>
          or, \quad \theta = \cos^{-1}\left(-\frac{1}{3}\right) = 109.5^{o}
         </me>
          </li>
       </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
</example>
</section>
